<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="148" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Muscle attachment scleritesnot developed, integument with wrinkled lineation, genital acetabula well developed, ac.2 larger than ac.1 and ac.3, capitulum with short rostrum; P-2 ventrodistal projections moderately long and bearing two fine setae, near base of projection there is short, thick seta; P-3 ventral margin convex, P-4 longer than P-3, excretory pore sclerotized, leg claws with three clawlets.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="150" pageId="5" pageNumber="148" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,420,294,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Idiosoma colour yellow. Idiosoma oval and somewhat flattened. Muscle attachment sclerites not developed. Integument (
<figureCitation box="[516,598,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) with wrinkled lineation. Setae 
<emphasis box="[961,1005,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fch</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1021,1101,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) short, thick, other idiosomal setae thin (
<figureCitation box="[271,402,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Figs 12–13</figureCitation>
). Trichobotria 
<emphasis box="[565,596,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fp</emphasis>
situated on small sclerites, and trichobothria 
<emphasis box="[1101,1129,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Oi</emphasis>
on relatively large sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
Anterior coxal groups (
<figureCitation box="[455,535,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) close to each other but not fused, with straight posteromedial margins, apodemes slightly developed. Sclerites bearing setae 
<emphasis box="[626,659,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Hv</emphasis>
situated near posterolateral angles of coxae II. Posterior coxal groups widely separated, glandularia 
<emphasis box="[489,519,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Pe</emphasis>
open at anteromedian angle of coxae III. Genital field situated between posterior coxal groups, with three pairs of unequal acetabula, ac.2 larger than ac.1 and ac.3 (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1163,546,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Gonopore shorter than genital flaps.Anterior and posterior genital sclerites small and subequal in shape and size. Each genital flap with about 28–30 median and three fine lateral setae. Pregenital sclerite very small, postgenital sclerite relatively large and unsclerotized. Excretory pore surrounded by sclerotized ring (
<figureCitation box="[893,976,654,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
Capitulum with a short rostrum, ventral margin of capitular base convex, lateral surface with several lineations (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,726,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Both pairs of hypostomal setae subequal in length. Chelicera basal segment large, chela crescent-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,762,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,969]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
Pedipalp rather slender (
<figureCitation box="[476,561,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[161,1427,992,1937]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 19, pedipalp; 20, IV-Leg-3–6; 21, leg claw. Scale bar: 1, 2, 3–5, 6 = 50 μm, 7, 8 = 20 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
): P-1 short and without setae; P-2 large, with six thick subequal dorsal setae, ventrodistal projections long and bearing two fine distal and thick proximal seta which shorter than projection; P-3ventral margin convex, with three thick dorsoproximal setae and one or two thin dorsodistal setae; P-4 slender and longer than P-3, with several rather long dorsodistal and ventrodistal fine setae, ventral margin with two small tubercles bearing short subequal peg-like setae.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="148" startId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" targetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1960,2021]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,699,1960,1985]" pageId="5" pageNumber="148">
FIGURES 19–21. 
