<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
Legs slender, especially posterior pair, III–IV-Leg-3–5 with rather numerous long dorsal plumose dorsal setae (
<figureCitation box="[160,247,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[161,1427,992,1937]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 19, pedipalp; 20, IV-Leg-3–6; 21, leg claw. Scale bar: 1, 2, 3–5, 6 = 50 μm, 7, 8 = 20 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Leg claws with three unequal pointed clawlets, dorsal clawlet a little longer than median and ventral clawlets, lamella slightly developed with strong concave ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[971,1054,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[161,1427,992,1937]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 19, pedipalp; 20, IV-Leg-3–6; 21, leg claw. Scale bar: 1, 2, 3–5, 6 = 50 μm, 7, 8 = 20 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Measurement (n=1). Idiosoma L 810; capitulum L 150, rostrum L 25; genital flap L 160, genital acetabula (ac.1–ac.3) L: 50, 62, 45; cheliceral segments: base L 160, chela L 50; pedipalp segments (P-1–5) L: 32, 95, 112, 150, 37; legs segments L: I-Leg-1–6: 60, 75, 100, 160, 175, 160; II-Leg-1–6: 60, 75, 110, 185, 200, 185; III-Leg- 1–6: 60, 75, 125, 225, 235, 210; IV-Leg-1–6: 125, 135, 150, 275, 250, 225.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,789]" box="[199,415,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Female: Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">
R 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[218,314,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">emarks.</emphasis>
The present species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[701,852,439,465]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[701,852,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of the integument. Differences between the two species are found in the following characters (character states of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sokolow" authorityYear="1940" box="[1044,1193,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1193,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">S. tridentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given in parentheses, data from 
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow, I. I." box="[266,433,511,537]" pageId="7" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 511" refId="ref3946" refString="Sokolow, I. I. (1940) [Hydracarina. Part I: Hydrachnellae. In: Fauna of the USSR. Paukoobraznye 5 (2). Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, pp. 1 - 511. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1940">Sokolow 1940</bibRefCitation>
): P-2 distoventral projecting with two fine distal setae and short, thick seta, 
<figureCitation box="[1282,1362,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[161,1427,992,1937]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 19, pedipalp; 20, IV-Leg-3–6; 21, leg claw. Scale bar: 1, 2, 3–5, 6 = 50 μm, 7, 8 = 20 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) (with three fine setae, thick seta near projection absent, 
<figureCitation box="[706,785,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
), P-3 ventral margin convex (straight), P-4 longer than P- 3 (P-4 shorter than P-3), genital acetabula large and located close to each other (comparatively small and distinctly separated), capitulum with short rostrum, 
<figureCitation box="[618,697,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[192,1388,391,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-62@4.[182,1406,381,1897]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 10, fragment of integument; 11, seta Fch; 12, idiocomal seta associated with glandularia; 13, trichobothria Oi; 14, coxal plates, left side; 15, genital field; 16, excretory pore; 17, capitulum, lateral view; 18, chelicera. Scale bars: 10–13, 16 = 50 μm, 14–15, 17–18 = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756114/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
(long and a little shorter than capitular base), claw lamella ventral margin strong concave, 
<figureCitation box="[420,499,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–21" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[174,1417,1000,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[161,1427,992,1937]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–21. Sperchon (Sperchon) smiti sp. n., male: 19, pedipalp; 20, IV-Leg-3–6; 21, leg claw. Scale bar: 1, 2, 3–5, 6 = 50 μm, 7, 8 = 20 μm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756116/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
(lamella ventral margin straight, 
<figureCitation box="[873,957,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[227,1364,196,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[206,1381,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Sperchon, adults: S. tridentatus: 22, pedipalp; 23, leg claw (after Sokolow 1940); S. minor: 24, idiosoma, dorsal view; 25, idiosoma, ventral view; 26, pedipalp (after Tuzovsky 2003)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756118/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="150">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
